LOW|internal/astgroup/parsers/src/pyparser/main.go:90|Indentation width counts each space as 1 and each tab as a flat +8 regardless of column. The Python tokenizer advances a tab to the next multiple of 8, so space-then-tab is column 8 there but 9 here. Files mixing tabs and spaces can compute inconsistent indent values, causing build to misnest blocks and emit spurious leaf stmt nodes via the defensive branch.|Expand tabs to the next multiple of 8 (indent += 8 - (indent % 8)) to match the Python tokenizer, or reject/flag tab-space-mixed indentation.|error-handling|15|internal/astgroup/parsers/src/pyparser/main.go:85-96|claude
LOW|internal/astgroup/parsers/src/goparser/main.go:39|The guest pins alloc'd buffers and hands the host int32(uintptr(unsafe.Pointer(&b[0]))) as a stable guest offset, valid only because the current Go GC is non-moving. This is an undocumented runtime invariant, not a language guarantee; a future moving GC makes the packed pointer a dangling offset with no detection. The unsafe alloc/free/emit/node boilerplate is copy-pasted across goparser, pyparser, and the 13.4 brace parsers, so any ABI fix must be applied N times.|Extract the shared alloc/free/emit/pins ABI into one internal guest package imported by every parser main.go, and add a build-time note pinning the GC assumption (or switch to an explicitly reserved arena).|maintainability|120|internal/astgroup/parsers/src/goparser/main.go:39-53|claude
